         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that there do not exist integration rules of the form &lt;latex&gt;$\int^\infty_0 f(x) dx = \sum_{i=1}^n w_if(x_i) + C_nf^{(m)}(\xi),\quad 0 &lt; \xi &lt; \infty$&lt;/latex&gt;.</p>
